Using the external stress thresholds of 110, 120 and 131 MPa, we further translate the propagated stress distributions into exceedance-based risk metrics. Under the main threshold of 131 MPa, the forward-UQ exceedance probability is 0.6396 for Level 0 and 0.6453 for Level 2. Under the stricter 120 MPa threshold, the corresponding risks increase to 0.7243 and 0.7326, and under 110 MPa they further increase to 0.8026 and 0.8118. Thus, the two models produce a qualitatively consistent safety picture, but the regularized Level 2 model yields a slightly more conservative high-stress tail. This result motivates the threshold-based interpretation developed in the next subsection. \
