We finally examine whether observation-driven posterior inference can translate stress constraints into parameter-space restriction. The reduced inverse benchmark is carried out on 20 held-out synthetic cases using four calibration parameters. Across these cases, the mean acceptance rate is 0.628, the mean absolute observation-fit error is 1.227, and the mean observable coverage90 is 1.0. The mean posterior safety-feasible fraction is 0.1667 under the 131 MPa threshold, 0.0792 under 120 MPa, and 0.0373 under 110 MPa. These averages already indicate that tighter safety criteria strongly compress the admissible posterior region. \uc0\u12304 At present, the uploaded comparison table contains only the reduced run; if a full inverse benchmark is added later, this paragraph should be expanded into an explicit full-versus-reduced comparison.\u12305  \
