English\
The case-wise results show the same trend more clearly. When the observed stress is 96.34 MPa, the feasible posterior fraction at 131 MPa is still 1.0. As the observed stress increases to 119.44, 127.34 and 133.39 MPa, this fraction drops to 0.8725, 0.6692 and 0.5508. Once the observed stress enters the clearly unsafe regime, the feasible fraction collapses rapidly: it is 0.0167 at 145.35 MPa, 0.0058 at 147.9 MPa, and becomes zero for several cases above 155 MPa, including 155.34, 158.66, 165.8 and 244.17 MPa. Thus, the posterior does not merely shift continuously with the observation; instead, the safety-feasible region contracts sharply once the observed stress crosses the neighborhood of the main threshold. \
